    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2622508539" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2622508539" />
    <a title="Lucie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/78969659-lucie"><img alt="Lucie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621970328p2/78969659.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2622508539?book_show_action=true">Dec 10, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lucie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lucie" href="/user/show/78969659-lucie">Lucie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781451621389" href="/book/show/17225848-brain-on-fire">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/78969659-lucie?shelf=autobiographical-memoir">autobiographical-memoir</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/78969659-lucie?shelf=award-winner">award-winner</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/78969659-lucie?shelf=survival">survival</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2622508539" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer306886837930383611"><b>“Her brain is on fire,&quot; he repeated. &quot;Her brain is under attack by her own body.”</b><br/><br/>This is a terrifying true account of how one woman&apos;s body betrayed her.<br/><br/>Approximately 50 million Americans (or one in five people) suffer from some form of autoimmune disease. Women are more likely to be affected than men. By some estimates, women make up 75% of those who are affected by autoimmune disease.<br/><br/>This gets pretty clinical in places, but the medical mystery keeps you hooked. One of the most important take-aw</span>
  <span id="freeText306886837930383611" style="display:none"><b>“Her brain is on fire," he repeated. "Her brain is under attack by her own body.”</b><br /><br />This is a terrifying true account of how one woman's body betrayed her.<br /><br />Approximately 50 million Americans (or one in five people) suffer from some form of autoimmune disease. Women are more likely to be affected than men. By some estimates, women make up 75% of those who are affected by autoimmune disease.<br /><br />This gets pretty clinical in places, but the medical mystery keeps you hooked. One of the most important take-aways from this account is to remain diligent. Never stop fighting for yourself and your loved ones. Keep searching, keep asking questions, and never give up.</span>
  <a data-text-id="306886837930383611" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


